🧠 Deep Understanding (INTERVIEW GOLD)
✔ 1. Absolute vs Relative Time
Type	Example
Absolute	UTC timestamp
Relative	“last 5 minutes”

👉 Systems should always rely on absolute time internally.

✔ 2. Timezone Problem (CRITICAL)

👉 Same timestamp = different meaning

10:00 IST ≠ 10:00 UTC

💬 GS Answer:

“I always store timestamps in UTC and convert to local time only at the presentation layer to avoid inconsistencies.”

✔ 3. DST (Daylight Saving)

👉 Time jumps forward/back

missing hour
duplicate hour

💬 GS Answer:

“I rely on timezone-aware libraries to handle DST instead of manually calculating offsets.”

✔ 4. Precision Issues
Type	Problem
Seconds	not enough
Milliseconds	preferred
Microseconds	high precision

👉 Trading systems require high precision timestamps

✔ 5. Ordering Problem

👉 Logs/events may arrive out of order

💬 GS Answer:

“I use event time (timestamp) instead of processing time and rely on ordering logic or watermarking in streaming systems.”

⚙️ Real-Time Usage
✔ Trading Systems
order sequencing
latency measurement
✔ Distributed Systems
event ordering
consistency
✔ Logging Systems
debugging timelines
